The paper deals with control and stability analysis of DC microgrids, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of L1 adaptive controllers and distributed consensus-based secondary control suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of power systems (cs.PF) and embedded systems (cs.ET). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which could place it in the sub-categories of mathematical optimization (cs.MA) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
